The paper deals with a theoretical model for distributed storage management systems, which involves optimization algorithms and competitive analysis. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of weighted edges and bipartite graphs also indicates a possible connection to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of LP and Primal-Dual algorithms suggests a possible connection to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as well. Finally, the use of randomized algorithms and competitive analysis suggests a possible connection to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
